<p><b>What is the field of biomedical instrumentation?</b> Biomedical instrumentation applies engineering and technology to solve medical problems in diagnosis, treatment, and disease prevention. The field combines principles of biophysics and biochemistry—where physics and chemistry meet biology—with medical and engineering practices.</p>